page.title: 13Development of public transport in Fulham
page.content:
Now in 2011 bos transport in Fulham has dramatically developed in line with the rapid increase of upmarket new housing developments replacing derelict industrial and commercial sites.

The no. 11 bus still runs but in addition there are the 295 running North and South. The 28 similarly. The 22 running through Kings Road to Piccadilly, The 424 local bus.The 391 to Richmond. The 14 and 414 buse through the West End and the 211 to Waterloo.

There is a regular water bus fron the border with Chelsea and Fulham
